==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[acanthus]]'' < {{AGr.}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=acanthuses|pl2=acanthi}}

# {{botany}} A genus of [[herbaceous]] [[prickly]] plants with toothed leaves, (family Acanthaceae, order Scrophulariales) found in the south of Europe, Asia Minor, and India; includes [[bear's breech]].
# {{architecture}} An ornament resembling the [[foliage]] or leaves of the [[acanthus]] (''Acanthus spinosus''); &mdash; used in the capitals of the [[Corinthian]] and [[composite]] orders.

